.TH CAT 1 "2026-05-18" "OurOS" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cat \- concatenate files and print on the standard output
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cat
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Concatenate FILE(s) to standard output.  With no FILE, or when FILE
is \-, read standard input.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-number\fR
Number all output lines.
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-number\-nonblank\fR
Number non-empty output lines, overrides \fB\-n\fR.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-squeeze\-blank\fR
Suppress repeated empty output lines.
.TP
\fB\-E\fR, \fB\-\-show\-ends\fR
Display $ at end of each line.
.TP
\fB\-T\fR, \fB\-\-show\-tabs\fR
Display TAB characters as ^I.
.TP
\fB\-A\fR, \fB\-\-show\-all\fR
Equivalent to \fB\-ET\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
cat file1 file2          Concatenate two files
cat -n file              Show with line numbers
cat < input > output     Copy stdin to a file
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tac (1),
.BR head (1),
.BR tail (1)
.SH AUTHOR
OurOS Contributors.
